  "html": "<div class=\"fr-view\">\n<p><strong>Interrogatives part 1 </strong></p>\n<p>An interrogative is a function word used to ask a question, such as what, which, when, where, who, whom, whose, why and how.</p>\n<p>All of the words and phrases listed here cannot be used with 「は」especially, those used as subjects, they should always be marked with「が」.</p>\n<p><img class=\"fr-dib\" src=\"https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/259/bb7/425/1593150866216.jpg\" style=\"width: auto; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" srcset=\"https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/259/bb7/425/1593150866216.jpg?width=1920 1x, https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/259/bb7/425/1593150866216.jpg?width=1920&amp;dpr=2 2x, https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/259/bb7/425/1593150866216.jpg?width=1920&amp;dpr=3 3x\"></p>\n<p>「どちら」is used as a polite form of 「だれ」 and 「どこ」, like 「こちら」 in Day 1.</p>\n<p>You can download a copy of this cheat sheet <a class=\"fr-file\" href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/thinkific/file_uploads/259518/attachments/b6b/b1d/39c/interrogatives_A.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">here,</a> </p>\n</div>",
